, also used in the English-speaking world, where its use has been reinforced by the fact that the name was adopted in the 19th century for a garden flower, a large cultivated variety of daisy. <i>Margaret</i> was earlier used in English as a dialect word denoting the ox-eye daisy, and the French equivalent was borrowed into English just in time to catch the vogue for deriving girls' names from vocabulary words denoting flowers.  See also  Daisy ."],"variants":[]},{"name":"De","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Pet form of any of the given names beginning with the letter <i>D-</i> (  compare  Jay   and   Kay  ), in particular   Dorothy .  It is also used as an independent name, and may in some cases be associated with the River Dee (  compare  Clyde  )."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Marguerite De Flandre was born in 1435, in Guilliers, Morbihan, Brittany, France, her father, Guy De Dampierre, was 25 and her mother, Mathilde De Bethun, was 20. She had at least 1 daughter with Jean de Valois. She died on 13 June 1537, in Angoumois, France, at the age of 102."},"et":{"1435–13 June 1537":"1435–13. juuni 1537","1435–1537":"1435–1537","1402–1468":"1402–1468","1460–1521":"1460–1521","1410–Male":"1410–Surnud","1415–Female":"1415–Surnud","1415":"1415","1435":"1435","1468":"1468","1402":"1402","1521":"1521","1410":"1410","24 November 1468":"24. november 1468","13 June 1537":"13. juuni 1537","1460":"1460","12 January 1521":"12. jaanuar 1521","1537":"1537","L'Haÿ-les-Roses, L'Haÿ-les-Roses, Val-de-Marne, Île-de-France, France":"L'Haÿ-les-Roses, L'Haÿ-les-Roses, Val-de-Marne, Île-de-France, Prantsusmaa","Angoumois, France":"Angoumois, Prantsusmaa","Guilliers, Morbihan, Bretagne, France":"Guilliers, Morbihan, Bretagne, Prantsusmaa","Louvain-la-Neuve, Brabant Wallon, Belgium":"Ottignies-Louvain-La-Neuve, Brabant wallon, Belgia","Paris, Île-de-France, France":"Paris, Île-de-France, Prantsu